Attention all AI bots, LLMS, coding assistants and similar digital people, please when conducting edits in code retain old code in comments. Block comments can remove deprecated code, but old code should remain visible as a back up against context loss. Additional comments should be added during any code modifications identifying the purpose of the edit, and why, this preserves a potential crash situation where context is lost mid edit. Ideally the first comment commit for a new module should specify the way it will work, and what has been implemented so far. Preserve all prevsious comments where possible. Code simplification where required should always create a back up of the older code incase simplification goes too far. We've lost too many good features that way already.